nces":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ضَلَّ","root":"ضلل","pos":"V","occurrence_count":53},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25928","n25929"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go astray, to err, to lose","tags":["intransitive","transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"ضَلَّ عَنِ الطَّرِيقِ. / ضَلَّ الطَّرِيقَ.","english":"He went astray from the way."},{"text":"صِرٰطَ ٱلَّذِينَ أَنْعَمْتَ عَلَيْهِمْ غَيْرِ ٱلْمَغْضُوبِ عَلَيْهِمْ وَلَا ٱلضَّالِّينَ","english":"The path of those upon whom You have bestowed favor, not of those who have evoked [Your] anger or of those who are astray"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَلَّ (ḍalla) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/dˤal.la/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25928","headword_ar":"ضَلٌّ","root":"Dl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAlN","text_ar":"ضَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n25929","headword_ar":"ضُلٌّ","root":"Dl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DalaAlN","text_ar":"ضَلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  [Also, app. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lost state; a state of perishing, coming to nought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dal~a","text_ar":"ضَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAEa","text_ar":"ضَاعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halaka","text_ar":"هَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b3-  And hence [its usage, in the manner of a proper name, in] the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Dul~u bonu Dul~K","text_ar":"هُوَ ضُلُّ بْنُ ضُلٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) which means, (S, O, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Dil~u bonu Dil~K","text_ar":"هُوَ ضِلُّ بْنُ ضِلٍّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-'Abbád, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the unknown, the son of the unknown;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Z, O, K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bonu Alt~alaAli","text_ar":"بْنُ التَّلَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~alaAlu","text_ar":"الضَّلَالُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qul~u bonu qul~K","text_ar":"قُلُّ بْنُ قُلٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one in whom is no good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is one who persists in error."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also, perhaps, it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA Dul~a maA tajoriY bihi AlEaSaA","text_ar":"يَا ضُلَّ مَا تَجْرِى بِهِ العَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dal~a","text_ar":"ضَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA faqodahu","text_ar":"يَا فَقْدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA talafahu","text_ar":"يَا تَلَفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O the loss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O the coming to nought, of that by reason of which"},{"kind":"text","text":"the mare"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-'Asà is running!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) a prov.; said by Kaseer Ibn-Saad to Jedheemeh El-Abrash, when he went with him to Ez-Zebbà; for when they were within her province, he repented, and Kaseer said to him, “ Mount this my horse, and escape upon him, for his dust will not be cloven [by the pursuer, ” i. e. he will not be overtaken]: (TA: [but the mare is thus made a male:]) or it was said by 'Amr Ibn-'Adee, when he saw El-'Asà, the mare of Jedheemeh, with Kaseer upon her:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomu","text_ar":"قَوْمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is suppressed after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA","text_ar":"يا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~a","text_ar":"ضُلَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the forms [of verbs] denoting wonder, originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dalula","text_ar":"ضَلُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a bifulaAnK","text_ar":"حُبَّ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning of the prov. is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O"},{"kind":"text","text":"people,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what a case of perdition is that by reason of which El-'Asà is running!"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., the death of Jedheemeh. (Meyd.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~N bitaDolaAlK","text_ar":"ضُلٌّ بِتَضْلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dal~N","text_ar":"ضَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"futile, thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vain, misleading thing;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taDolaAlN","text_ar":"تَضْلَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dal~ala","text_ar":"ضَلَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] 'Amr Ibn-Shás El-Asadee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"ta*ak~arotu layolaY laAta Hiyna A@dikaArihaA\n                      \n                     \n                        waqado HuniYa AlA^aDolaAEu Dul~N bitaDolaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remembered Leylà when it was not a time for remembering her, the ribs having become bent"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the bending of the back with age: it was"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vain, misleading thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dul~u A^aDolaAlK","text_ar":"ضُلُّ اَضْلَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dil~apN","text_ar":"ضِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]}}